checkIntegrity

public java.lang.String checkIntegrity()
Check the consistency of this object respect to the problem implemented. It's automaticly called before computation by the validate routine. Subclasses of this object could overwrite it to implement specific checking that must be done before starting computation.

Overrides:
checkIntegrity in class XRDcat
Returns:
the status of the checking; null if all it's ok, a message with the problem otherwise.
